Table reading and preprocessing

chains <- read.csv("chains_evaluation.csv", stringsAsFactors = TRUE) |>
  dplyr::select(chain_id, pdb_id, label, AF_average_pLDDT, OF_average_pLDDT, EF_average_pLDDT, AF_TM_score, OF_TM_score, EF_TM_score, AF_RMSD, OF_RMSD, EF_RMSD) |>
  setNames(c("chain_id", "pdb_id", "label",
             "AlphaFold_pLDDT", "OmegaFold_pLDDT", "ESMFold_pLDDT",
             "AlphaFold_TMscore", "OmegaFold_TMscore", "ESMFold_TMscore",
             "AlphaFold_RMSD", "OmegaFold_RMSD", "ESMFold_RMSD"))

Correlations

AlphaFold

chains |>
  dplyr::select(AlphaFold_pLDDT, AlphaFold_TMscore, AlphaFold_RMSD) |>
  ggpairs(upper = list(continuous = "points"), lower = list(continuous = "points"), diag = list(continuous = "densityDiag"))

Z <- as.matrix(chains |> dplyr::select(AlphaFold_pLDDT, AlphaFold_TMscore, AlphaFold_RMSD))
R <- rcorr(Z)
diag(R$P) <- 0
ggcorrplot(R$r, p.mat = R$P, title = "Pearson's correlations", 
  lab = TRUE, type = "full", method = "square", outline.color = "white", show.legend = FALSE, pch.cex = 10)
